properties.Title: Blizzard Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: A potent winter storm will impact southern Kivalliq on Sunday and into Monday. This storm will bring strong northwesterly winds with gusts up to 90 km/h. These strong winds will lead to significantly reduced visibilities in blowing snow, creating blizzard conditions. These winds will gradually diminish late on Monday and visibilities will improve. ### Travel is expected to be hazardous due to reduced visibility. Blizzard warnings are issued when widespread reduced visibilities of 400 metres or less are expected for at least 6 hours. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to NUstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #NUStorm.

properties.Title: Special Weather Statement In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Heavy snow, possibly mixed with rain, arrives tonight. A low pressure system will pass just south of Manitoulin Island tonight and give periods of snow and about 10 centimetres by Monday morning. The snow will begin early this evening and become heavy later this evening. Some rain may mix in with the snow overnight. The west end of the island may receive 8 to 10 centimetres however the east end may receive just over 10 centimetres of heavy wet snow by Monday morning. Travel is expected to be difficult tonight and early Monday morning due to rapidly accumulating snowfall. Snowfall warnings are in effect north of the region, in Espanola, and a snowfall warning may be required for Manitoulin Island if 15 or more centimetres is expected tonight. ### Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to ONstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #ONStorm.

properties.Title: Winter Storm Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: A potent winter storm will impact southern Baffin Island beginning tonight. The storm will bring significant winds, with gusts in excess of 90 km/h possible. This system will also bring 10 to 20 cm of snow. These winds combined with the falling snow will lead to significantly reduced visibilities in blowing snow, creating near blizzard conditions for Iqaluit. Conditions will gradually improve Sunday evening. ### Rapidly accumulating snow could make travel difficult over some locations. Visibility may be suddenly reduced at times in heavy snow. Winter storm warnings are issued when multiple types of severe winter weather are expected to occur together. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to NUstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #NUStorm.

properties.Summary:
Description: A potent winter storm will impact southern Baffin Island and northern Kivalliq beginning tonight. This storm will bring significant winds, with gusts in excess of 90 km/h likely. These winds combined with falling snow will lead to significantly reduced visibilities in blowing snow, creating blizzard conditions. The blizzard will end at Kimmirut and Kinngait Sunday morning but snow will continue to accumulate into the afternoon. The blizzard at Coral Harbour will continue tonight and through Sunday and will weaken somewhat Sunday night. The blizzard will start overnight at Naujaat and continue through Sunday and most of Monday. ### Travel is expected to be hazardous due to reduced visibility. Blizzard warnings are issued when widespread reduced visibilities of 400 metres or less are expected for at least 6 hours. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to NUstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #NUStorm.

properties.Summary:
Description: An extended blizzard for most of Kivalliq beginning today. An intense winter storm centred over northern Quebec will bring increasing winds and blizzard conditions to Kivalliq beginning this morning. Bitterly cold wind chills will also develop.
